CommonFields.Title: Polyamide-silica nanocomposites: mechanical, morphological and thermomechanical investigations
Author: Sarwar, Muhammad Ilyas
Zulfiqar, Sonia
Ahmad, Zahoor
CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemistry, Quaid-i-Azam University, Islamabad 45320, Pakistan

Mixing.Description: 10 g of neat resin was dissolved with 65 g of DMF in a sealed conical flask equipped with a stirrer.

ChooseParameter.Other: Mixture was agitated for 5 days at 35 C under anhydrous conditions

Mixing.Description: TEOS was added to mixture and stirred.

Additive.Description: Diethylamine was used as a catalyst to initiate hydrolysis and condensation

Amount.description: A stoichiometric amount of water mixed with 5 wt percent of diethylamine

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Films were cast into Petri dishes by evaporating solvent.
